R0Cx8zNhMjf_kBd9i0HyyW6cgh9gnEwh1FDZymARrfU=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java resources**\\n\\nI'm considering how my agent might include a dependency jar resource. The test should verify that the payload starts with CAFEBABE, but the resource comes from the library jar. I'm thinking about how I can request the active class file and whether using getClass().getResourceAsStream(\\\"/javassist/tools/web/Webserver.class\\\") can work in Native with metadata. This method avoids referencing the test resource, but I need to clarify the generated metadata for the library class resource. Good to think through!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_tM2YqujD7ZCbjEJg7Ww0jd7K|fc_09fee34e639779f40169f9fe0f890c81a3b444177af4583042", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist/javassist/ViewerTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 762, "output": 1521, "cacheRead": 13312, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 15595, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777991161095, "responseId": "resp_09fee34e639779f40169f9fdf9772081a39bdf0c756241c623"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_tM2YqujD7ZCbjEJg7Ww0jd7K|fc_09fee34e639779f40169f9fe0f890c81a3b444177af4583042", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage javassist.javassist;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.PrintStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n\nimport javassist.tools.web.Viewer;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ViewerTest {\n    @Test\n    void runLoadsViewerThroughItsClassLoaderAndInvokesMain() throws Throwable {\n        Viewer viewer = new Viewer(\"127.0.0.1\", 1);\n        PrintStream originalError = System.err;\n        ByteArrayOutputStream errorOutput = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n\n        try (PrintStream replacementError = new PrintStream(errorOutput, true, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)) {\n            System.setErr(replacementError);\n\n            viewer.run(Viewer.class.getName(), new String[0]);\n        } finally {\n            System.setErr(originalError);\n        }\n\n        assertThat(viewer.getServer()).isEqualTo(\"127.0.0.1\");\n        assertThat(viewer.getPort()).isOne();\n        assertThat(errorOutput.toString(StandardCharsets.UTF_8)).contains(\"Usage: java javassist.tools.web.Viewer\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadClassDelegatesCoreJavaClassesToTheSystemLoader() throws Exception {\n        Viewer viewer = new Viewer(\"127.0.0.1\", 1);\n\n        Class<?> loadedClass = viewer.loadClass(String.class.getName());\n\n        assertThat(loadedClass).isSameAs(String.class);\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777991184036}]}
